{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id7851bc49-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s583j–9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"583j–9"},"text":"§ 583j–9.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Federal funds","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For fiscal year 2014 and thereafter, the National Forest Foundation may hold Federal funds made available but not immediately disbursed and may use any interest or other investment income earned (before, on, or after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-01-17"},"text":"January 17, 2014","children":[],"tail":") on Federal funds to carry out the purposes of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/593"},"text":"Public Law 101–593","children":[],"tail":": "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided further","children":[],"tail":", That such investments may be made only in interest-bearing obligations of the United States or in obligations guaranteed as to both principal and interest by the United States."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id7851bc4a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/76/dG/tIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–76, div. G, title III","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-01-17"},"text":"Jan. 17, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/327"},"text":"128 Stat. 327","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id7851bc4b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id7851bc4c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id7851bc4d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/593"},"text":"Public Law 101–593","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/593"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–593","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-16"},"text":"Nov. 16, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/2954"},"text":"104 Stat. 2954","children":[],"tail":", which enacted this subchapter, chapter 32A of this title, and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s777e–1"},"text":"section 777e–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":", amended sections 2910, 3702, 3709, 4403, and 4404 of this title, and enacted provisions listed in a table of National Wildlife Refuges set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s668dd"},"text":"section 668dd of this title","children":[],"tail":" and provisions set out in notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s3701"},"text":"section 3701 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s4321"},"text":"section 4321 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id7851bc4e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Department of the Interior, Environment, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, 2014, and also as part of the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2014, and not as part of the National Forest Foundation Act which comprises this subchapter."